==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Recreative
<hw>Rec"re*a`tive</hw> <pr>(r?k"r?*?`t?v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧cr⟦eacute⟧atif</ets>. See <er>Recreate</er>.]</ety>
<def>Tending to recreate or refresh; recreating; giving new vigor or
animation; reinvigorating; giving relief after labor or pain; amusing;
diverting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let the music of them be <qex>recreative</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>--- <wordforms><wf>Rec"re*a`tive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Rec"re*a`tive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recrement</ent>⟦br⟧
